Meet <b>Seliat</b>, our Citizen of the Week!<br><br>Seliat lives in Metro Park in a beautiful blue house at <a href='/home/?user=sweetiseli93'>44566-C Main Street</a>. This central location allows her to dash into downtown Millsberry at a moment's notice for spur-of-the-moment games of basketball. A citizen of Millsberry since October 28, 2006, Seliat is a fun girl with a lot of knowledge to share.<br><br>Even though school is out, Seliat is still doing a lot of reading, one of her favorite hobbies. She enjoys both fiction and non-fiction, and loves to discuss what she finds most interesting with her friends, or with Carla Robbins, the owner of <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=2">Bookends Bookshop</a>. <br><br>Another of her passions is singing. Rap, R&B and reggae are her favorite musical genres, and she has trained herself to sing in these very different styles. This summer she's excited to hang out with her friends, shop, and relax a bit. She pushes herself hard during the school year to do her best in every class, so she deserves a nice long summer vacation.<br><br>Sometimes her friends ask her why she doesn't add more rooms to her home, but she says that her current setup is just perfect. If you have something you think will look nice in her home, send her a package. After all, who doesn't like gifts?<br><br>Thanks for being a good citizen, Seliat, and congrats on being named Citizen of the Week!</div>
